try to overtake me?

26
00:05:26,533 --> 00:05:30,366
Watch out, hero.
What a strange mechanic!

27
00:05:42,240 --> 00:05:45,156
Hi, Mr. Braganza.
- Hello, Albert.

28
00:05:46,573 --> 00:05:48,337
Is the car giving you trouble?

29
00:05:48,387 --> 00:05:50,847
- No, with you around,
what trouble will it give?

30
00:05:50,989 --> 00:05:53,697
Is your Mercedes doing fine?
- Yes, it is.

31
00:05:53,991 --> 00:05:56,032
How's everyone at home?
-fine.

32
00:05:58,004 --> 00:05:59,743
And how is Stella?
- She is fine.

33
00:05:59,793 --> 00:06:00,694
And Dominic?

34
00:06:00,745 --> 00:06:04,369
That problem of yours..
- It has been solved. Thanks a lot.

35
00:06:04,529 --> 00:06:07,071
I see. Go ahead.
I'm waiting for the bill.

36
00:06:07,154 --> 00:06:09,199
Okay, Mr. Braganza. Bye.
- Bye.

37
00:06:18,111 --> 00:06:20,528
Buddy, bring me
a cup of special tea quickly.

38
00:06:23,002 --> 00:06:25,737
fast, fast.

39
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:33,693
Albert, your girlfriend had called.

40
00:06:35,318 --> 00:06:39,068
When?
- About 15 minutes back.

41
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:51,608
She said she can't meet you this
evening. She has to attend a party.

42
00:06:51,659 --> 00:06:52,824
Must be a dance party.

43
00:06:52,875 --> 00:06:55,074
why do you care?
I gave him the message na.

44
00:07:00,774 --> 00:07:04,731
Has this milk split?
what's this Seth (business owner)?

45
00:07:06,152 --> 00:07:09,442
The milk in my tea is okay.
Something's wrong with his.

46
00:07:10,305 --> 00:07:12,764
Albert, what will you do
this evening?

47
00:07:18,398 --> 00:07:23,359
Don't charge me for this tea!
- Albert, what will you do this evening?

48
00:07:23,629 --> 00:07:25,782
Albert!

49
00:07:25,997 --> 00:07:29,110
I will think about it.
I am not an alcoholic like you.

50
00:07:29,291 --> 00:07:31,407
Every evening with
mosambi (country liquor).

51
00:07:32,021 --> 00:07:33,275
Rascal!

52
00:07:34,537 --> 00:07:36,361
Buddy, pick up the chair.

53
00:08:01,643 --> 00:08:04,309
Move, move!
Can't you see the car?

54
00:08:38,443 --> 00:08:41,013
Why are you getting
involved in all of this?

55
00:08:41,185 --> 00:08:42,825
Please stay away from all of this.

56
00:08:43,138 --> 00:08:48,763
How can I stay away? I have to do
whatever the union decides.

57
00:08:48,941 --> 00:08:52,441
And is it that
we are demanding too much?

58
00:08:52,970 --> 00:08:58,928
Are we asking for millions, or
a bungalow, or a car?

59
00:08:59,532 --> 00:09:02,384
We demand a respectful life. that's it.
- Damn the strike!

60
00:09:02,454 --> 00:09:04,411
Will being on strike
give you respect?

61
00:09:05,574 --> 00:09:10,074
Forget about the strike. Mom,
will I get tea? - Yes, right away.

62
00:09:10,504 --> 00:09:13,378
Let me pack his lunch.
He'll get late for work.

63
00:09:14,293 --> 00:09:18,677
Try to understand.
There is so much Inflation.

64
00:09:19,007 --> 00:09:21,350
Shouldn't our salaries
also increase accordingly?

65
00:09:21,427 --> 00:09:25,342
Handsome salary and yearly bonus.
Can't we get that? - Yes, you can.

66
00:09:25,426 --> 00:09:26,759
But that's the union's job.

67
00:09:27,049 --> 00:09:29,322
Let them ask,
why are you getting into it?

68
00:09:29,967 --> 00:09:31,425
What if the mill shuts down?

69
00:09:31,509 --> 00:09:34,341
Why would it?
We haven't threatened them.

70
00:09:34,716 --> 00:09:37,216
Moreover, we have..
- This happens all the time.

71
00:09:37,300 --> 00:09:39,341
Your demands will never get met.

72
00:09:39,392 --> 00:09:41,342
Then you'll strike work.
The mill will be closed.

73
00:09:41,393 --> 00:09:44,183
I tell you the union
won't do anything.

74
00:09:44,254 --> 00:09:47,551
Mom, let him at least complete the point.
- What's the point?

75
00:09:48,241 --> 00:09:49,997
Mom is absolutely right.

76
00:09:50,610 --> 00:09:54,151
Calling for strike
is the work of crazy people.

77
00:09:55,456 --> 00:09:58,423
We aren't like them.
We are better off than them.

78
00:09:58,506 --> 00:10:01,089
Have your tea.
- Look at me.

79
00:10:03,204 --> 00:10:06,463
There was a strike at the garage.
I stayed away from it.

80
00:10:06,727 --> 00:10:09,963
I had nothing to do with it.
I do my job, I get my salary.

81
00:10:15,490 --> 00:10:19,971
I'm the only mechanic in Mumbai who
delivers the car to the customer's house.

82
00:10:20,902 --> 00:10:22,526
I get to drive the car.

83
00:10:24,141 --> 00:10:27,686
I am acquainted with
several millionaires.

84
00:10:28,693 --> 00:10:31,802
I don't address them formally.

85
00:10:33,459 --> 00:10:35,953
I don't have to.
I call them by their first names.

86
00:10:36,003 --> 00:10:38,514
Vivek, Murad, their first names.
Like that.

87
00:10:42,044 --> 00:10:44,294
Really Albert, you are
such a fool.

88
00:10:45,605 --> 00:10:48,440
What did you say?
- Fool.

89
00:10:51,567 --> 00:10:54,441
You are the bane of my life.
You and Dominic.

90
00:10:57,421 --> 00:11:00,458
Mom, I spoke to Vivek
about a job for Dominic.

91
00:11:00,542 --> 00:11:02,323
He promised he would look in to it.

92
00:11:02,717 --> 00:11:07,633
Where is Dominic? Where is he?
- Who knows?

93
00:11:19,437 --> 00:11:21,766
Aye, Dominic!

94
00:12:39,865 --> 00:12:41,447
Salaam Javed.
- Hi, Stella.

95
00:12:41,531 --> 00:12:43,739
How are you, Stella?
- Fine.

96
00:12:47,270 --> 00:12:49,884
How are you, Stella?
Albert is in the office.

97
00:12:50,291 --> 00:12:51,415
Thank you, Madhu.

98
00:13:22,125 --> 00:13:24,610
Hello Albert.

99
00:13:39,795 --> 00:13:41,461
Why didn't you answer my call?

100
00:13:44,058 --> 00:13:45,365
I was under the car.

101
00:13:47,852 --> 00:13:51,931
I have good news. I got a promotion.
- I see.

102
00:13:57,120 --> 00:14:00,575
I'm a secretary to the boss now.
- When did the party get over?

103
00:14:03,833 --> 00:14:05,990
Are you talking about the other night?
- Yes.

104
00:14:06,702 --> 00:14:09,112
At about 11:30 pm.

105
00:14:13,424 --> 00:14:14,816
How did you reach home?

106
00:14:17,742 --> 00:14:19,026
Arvind dropped me.

107
00:14:25,095 --> 00:14:27,865
Did you have fun? Did you?

108
00:14:30,055 --> 00:14:32,954
What fun?
All parties are similar.

109
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:41,338
Albert, I can't refuse
to attend the party.

110
00:14:43,547 --> 00:14:45,795
What would you do in my place?
-Did I stop you?

111
00:14:48,002 --> 00:14:50,163
why are you getting angry
unnecessarily?

112
00:14:52,494 --> 00:14:54,577
Okay tell me, what time
this evening?

113
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:56,525
I have loads of work.

114
00:14:58,299 --> 00:14:59,591
And tomorrow?

115
00:15:01,548 --> 00:15:05,090
Tomorrow also there's work.

116
00:15:06,332 --> 00:15:09,105
Will you let me know?

117
00:15:09,155 --> 00:15:12,655
This is done.
I'll call you if I get time.

118
00:15:15,363 --> 00:15:16,905
Okay?

119
00:15:21,590 --> 00:15:23,923
Have you had lunch?
- Not yet.

120
00:15:25,430 --> 00:15:28,638
Can I have lunch here?
- Yes, sure.

121
00:15:30,155 --> 00:15:32,655
Go ahead. Have I stopped you?

122
00:16:14,862 --> 00:16:18,127
Now a days there are
more meetings, less work, eh?

123
00:16:23,338 --> 00:16:24,879
Darn him.

124
00:16:45,957 --> 00:16:49,457
Please keep it away son,
you know Albert doesn't like it.

125
00:16:51,297 --> 00:16:55,855
"Okay, Albert doesn't like it."

126
00:16:55,937 --> 00:17:00,495
"Okay, Albert doesn't like it."

127
00:17:03,171 --> 00:17:08,963
"Doesn't like this,
Doesn't like that"

128
00:17:09,420 --> 00:17:14,962
"You don't like anything I do."

129
00:17:15,503 --> 00:17:22,127
"This belongs to Albert.
That belongs to Joan."

130
00:17:23,252 --> 00:17:25,836
"Shall I help you?
Shall I sing a song?"

131
00:17:25,919 --> 00:17:30,460
"Shall I help you?
Shall I sing a song?"

132
00:17:30,543 --> 00:17:34,010
"Shall I help you?"
- You're mad.

133
00:17:34,275 --> 00:17:37,775
Nuts
-Nuts?

134
00:17:40,126 --> 00:17:43,459
"Dominic is nuts."

135
00:17:43,542 --> 00:17:46,501
So what? Who cares?
This world isn't for me.

136
00:17:46,584 --> 00:17:49,666
"This world isn't for me."

137
00:17:52,708 --> 00:17:57,083
"This world belongs to
working men, famous men."

138
00:17:57,166 --> 00:18:01,207
"This world belongs to
working men, famous men."

139
00:18:01,290 --> 00:18:02,838
That is right.

140
00:18:03,021 --> 00:18:07,602
You make fun of others
because you are jobless.

141
00:18:07,934 --> 00:18:11,434
See Joan, she also works.
At least she does something.

142
00:18:11,914 --> 00:18:16,206
"Joan! Nuts."

143
00:18:16,539 --> 00:18:20,622
"Dominic is nuts.
He is nuts."

144
00:18:21,247 --> 00:18:25,247
"Dominic is nuts.
He is nuts ."

145
00:18:53,100 --> 00:18:56,600
I like the colour of your Saree.
Is there anything in that colour?

146
00:18:58,593 --> 00:19:01,342
Red? Let me check.

147
00:19:10,345 --> 00:19:12,178
Your taste is classy.

148
00:19:12,284 --> 00:19:15,830
This is the color I want,
but the design isn't good.

149
00:19:16,587 --> 00:19:19,267
The sari is for my sister.

150
00:19:21,192 --> 00:19:24,960
It's her birthday today.
Will you choose one for her?

151
00:19:27,713 --> 00:19:31,814
You look so much like my sister.
In fact you look better.

152
00:19:33,255 --> 00:19:36,342
See, this sari would be
good for your sister.

153
00:19:36,849 --> 00:19:42,431
Great! That's the color I wanted.
Will you do me another favor?

154
00:19:45,264 --> 00:19:46,429
What?

155
00:19:48,433 --> 00:19:52,098
It's a small request.
Will you wear the sari for me?

156
00:19:54,510 --> 00:19:57,855
I want to know how beautiful
my sister would look.

157
00:20:04,477 --> 00:20:09,101
I will wear it.
I'm like your sister, right?

158
00:20:13,534 --> 00:20:15,576
And your sister is like me.

159
00:20:18,046 --> 00:20:19,765
Just like me?

160
00:20:34,039 --> 00:20:36,799
Is she lame like me too?

161
00:20:40,345 --> 00:20:42,135
Isn't she very pretty?

162
00:20:45,740 --> 00:20:47,199
Is she also handicapped?

163
00:21:16,872 --> 00:21:19,746
Just five more minutes, Albert.
This is the last letter.

164
00:21:21,475 --> 00:21:23,225
Yeah, that's alright.

165
00:21:50,739 --> 00:21:55,864
Well, forget it.
I'll complete it tomorrow.

166
00:22:02,868 --> 00:22:07,825
"Let our flag always fly high."

167
00:22:09,809 --> 00:22:12,059
Bombay.

168
00:22:12,955 --> 00:22:14,705
Where is Europe?

169
00:22:15,251 --> 00:22:18,520
Where are we going this evening?
London or Paris?

170
00:22:20,465 --> 00:22:22,629
Bombay is the best.

171
00:22:24,556 --> 00:22:29,347
Right? Our Bombay is best.

172
00:22:32,344 --> 00:22:35,272
Stella, why are you still here?

173
00:22:37,483 --> 00:22:41,045
I make you work too hard.
I'll take you out for a movie today.

174
00:22:43,542 --> 00:22:46,353
If you refuse, I'll carry you out.

175
00:22:46,629 --> 00:22:50,293
No. Arvind...
I can't come.

176
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:52,009
why?

177
00:22:52,612 --> 00:22:56,000
This is Albert.
Albert... Arvind.

178
00:22:57,375 --> 00:22:58,880
So, you are the Albert.

179
00:23:03,089 --> 00:23:06,004
I have heard a lot about you.
- I have also...

180
00:23:06,789 --> 00:23:11,041
You should have told me earlier.
We'll see the film some other day.

181
00:23:15,042 --> 00:23:16,800
Let's go Albert.

182
00:23:20,129 --> 00:23:21,130
Stella.

183
00:23:22,836 --> 00:23:26,948
When will you treat me with Goan food?
-After your trip to Singapore.

184
00:23:27,486 --> 00:23:29,486
Bye-bye.
- Okay.

185
00:23:36,840 --> 00:23:38,380
What did I do?

186
00:23:40,340 --> 00:23:42,840
What did I do?

187
00:23:44,125 --> 00:23:47,026
You don't understand..

188
00:23:47,130 --> 00:23:49,130
I cannot refuse to go.

189
00:23:49,797 --> 00:23:52,571
What would you do in my place?

190
00:23:52,629 --> 00:23:56,129
Stella, what would you do in my place?
Tell me that!

191
00:23:58,963 --> 00:24:00,628
I won't tolerate it.

192
00:24:03,629 --> 00:24:05,629
He talks rubbish.

193
00:24:06,954 --> 00:24:09,244
You can travel to Hong Kong and
Singapore with him.

194
00:24:09,295 --> 00:24:10,878
You get me wrong, Albert.

195
00:24:10,962 --> 00:24:14,377
I swear Arvind has never
misbehaved with me.

196
00:24:16,253 --> 00:24:20,669
He might not have.
But I know his type. All rascals.

197
00:24:22,377 --> 00:24:25,644
What can I do if someone
wants to take me to the movies?

198
00:24:25,709 --> 00:24:29,293
He's no ordinary man.
He's Arvind sir, Arvind Sir.

199
00:24:29,376 --> 00:24:32,001
He's rich. He's a businessman.

200
00:24:33,460 --> 00:24:38,249
Had I not been there, you would
have definitely gone with him.

201
00:24:39,240 --> 00:24:41,259
Albert would be toiling
there in the garage.

202
00:24:41,317 --> 00:24:44,774
You would've called and
told me you can't come.

203
00:24:44,834 --> 00:24:46,958
Don't lie Albert,
has it ever happened..

204
00:24:47,041 --> 00:24:49,583
..that I promised to come with you,
but went away with him?

205
00:24:49,666 --> 00:24:51,958
It was his idea to go
for a movie, not mine.

206
00:24:52,374 --> 00:24:55,916
So, you should have gone with him.
Why didn't you?

207
00:25:21,913 --> 00:25:25,413
In anger, you even stop thinking.
Will you even listen to me?

208
00:25:25,663 --> 00:25:29,079
He asked me out for a movie. I didn't.
- Yes, he asked you out.

209
00:25:29,162 --> 00:25:34,954
Why did he ask you? Why didn't he
ask me or others? Mind your dress.

210
00:25:36,494 --> 00:25:42,036
It's blowing away. I told you
to wear a sari. But you never listen.

211
00:25:42,828 --> 00:25:46,952
The men on the streets are staring
at you. - You are crazy.

212
00:25:47,035 --> 00:25:50,202
I wear these dresses because
I like them. Not for others.

213
00:25:51,459 --> 00:25:54,959
You have a response to everything
Albert says.

214
00:25:55,992 --> 00:25:59,172
What happens to you
in Arvind's presence?

215
00:25:59,222 --> 00:26:01,422
Why were you shut then?

216
00:26:01,472 --> 00:26:07,179
Stop it. I can't listen to this.
- You have to. You have to listen to me.

217
00:26:08,366 --> 00:26:10,616
Truth is always bitter.

218
00:26:11,366 --> 00:26:15,158
Don't cover your legs.
Why did you wear a skirt?

219
00:26:15,450 --> 00:26:19,199
Let it fly.
Have a look at my girlfriend's legs.

220
00:26:19,282 --> 00:26:20,949
Constable, you too look.

221
00:26:23,574 --> 00:26:26,573
Darn it! Let it fly off.

222
00:26:29,364 --> 00:26:30,948
I want to go home.

223
00:27:00,031 --> 00:27:01,406
Stella is back.
- Yes.

224
00:27:01,489 --> 00:27:04,448
Fill the form.
She will get it typed tomorrow.

225
00:27:06,232 --> 00:27:09,524
My God! I forgot a certificate.
- What?

226
00:27:09,697 --> 00:27:13,103
Certificate.
-For god's sake you forgot the certificate?

227
00:27:13,154 --> 00:27:15,975
You are great. You think going
to Canada is just like that?

228
00:27:16,568 --> 00:27:19,133
You don't understand.
How can you forget a certificate?

229
00:27:19,184 --> 00:27:21,526
Don't panic, dad.
- Panic? What panic?

230
00:27:21,762 --> 00:27:23,720
I'll get it done.
- All right.

231
00:27:34,440 --> 00:27:35,981
What's wrong, Stella?

232
00:27:46,586 --> 00:27:49,878
I'll go fill the form quickly
and give it to Stella.

233
00:28:12,861 --> 00:28:16,515
What's wrong, Stella? Did you get
into a fight with Albert again?

234
00:28:18,677 --> 00:28:23,271
Alice, how do I look in these clothes?
- You look very beautiful.

235
00:28:26,537 --> 00:28:29,245
Really?
- Yes, you look very beautiful.

236
00:28:57,823 --> 00:28:59,281
Can I borrow Rs. 10?

237
00:29:23,813 --> 00:29:25,312
I'll return it tomorrow.

238
00:29:27,330 --> 00:29:29,080
No need.

239
00:29:38,273 --> 00:29:40,360
Is my money bastardised?

240
00:29:52,403 --> 00:29:55,402
Joan, are you ashamed
that I am your brother?

241
00:30:01,013 --> 00:30:03,801
How does it matter
where I get the money from?

242
00:30:06,585 --> 00:30:10,210
Every person steals
in some way or other.

243
00:30:11,343 --> 00:30:16,184
